        "**Team**1 designer · 2 engineers · 1 PM"
      ],
      "body": [
        "**Tasktrox arrived** with a stack of Notion docs, a battle-scarred Trello board, and one question. Why does software for architects feel like software for accountants?",
        "The brief was deceptively simple: build a project-management tool that actually feels like the studios it serves. Tactile. Editorial. Quietly precise. Not another rectangle of tabs and toasts.",
        "We threw out the SaaS playbook on day one. **No purple gradients, no dashboard spaghetti, no AI-as-mascot.** Instead we anchored the system in the language architects already speak: gridlines, plates, sectional cuts, marginalia."
      ]
    },
    "vision": {
      "label": "The Vision",
      "titleLine1": "A workspace that respects",
      "titleLine2": "the",
      "titleAccent": "craft.",
      "body": [
        "Three principles shaped every screen. **One: replace dashboards with documents.** A studio thinks in artifacts, not metrics, so the product treats every project as a living folio you can mark up, not a feed you scroll past.",
        "**Two: make the chrome quiet.** Toolbars and toasts that earn their pixels. State changes that read as movement, not noise. **Three: keep the tool truthful.** If a number is provisional, say so. If a milestone slipped, show the slippage rather than recolour the badge."
      ]
    },
    "pull": {
